# Refined Blueprint — Sage Archetype Portfolio

## Purpose
Build a portfolio homepage that communicates front-end depth in 10-15 seconds through clarity, precision, and calm visual authority.

This document rewrites and QA-refines the original blueprint to be:
- actionable for build execution
- explicit for Desktop and Mobile behavior
- aligned with a clean, efficient UX and engineering standards

---

## QA Summary of the Original Blueprint

What was strong:
- clear brand archetype and tone
- coherent visual direction
- strong emphasis on proof over decoration
- sensible modern stack

What needed refinement for execution:
- missing concrete responsive rules (breakpoints, spacing, column collapse behavior)
- no explicit content length constraints (headline/body limits)
- no measurable acceptance criteria per section
- no interaction/accessibility checklist mapped to components
- no implementation sequence to reduce decision friction

This refined version resolves those gaps.

---

## Product Goal

A single-page portfolio that feels:
- intelligent
- minimal
- architectural
- calm
- technically mature

Primary user outcomes:
1. Recruiter quickly understands specialty and quality.
2. Hiring manager sees proof of advanced front-end capability.
