## Visual System

### Color Tokens
Use one restrained accent only.

- Background 900: #0B0D10
- Background 800: #111315
- Surface 700: #1A1D21
- Surface 600: #20242A
- Text Primary: #F5F7FA
- Text Secondary: #A7B0BC
- Text Muted: #6B7280
- Accent: #A3E635

Rules:
- Accent appears only in links, active nav, focused controls, and small indicators.
- Avoid full-screen saturated gradients.
- Keep contrast WCAG AA minimum.

### Typography
Primary recommendation:
- Headings: Geist or Satoshi
- Body: Inter or IBM Plex Sans
- Optional mono accent: JetBrains Mono (metadata only)

Type scale guidance:
- H1 desktop: 52-64px, mobile: 34-40px
- H2 desktop: 32-40px, mobile: 26-30px
- Body: 16-18px desktop, 15-16px mobile
- Line length target: 55-75 characters desktop, 35-50 mobile

### Spacing and Rhythm
- Use 8px spacing system
- Section vertical padding desktop: 96-140px
- Section vertical padding mobile: 64-88px
- Max content width: 1120-1200px

---

## Responsive Layout Rules (Desktop + Mobile)

Breakpoints:
- Mobile: 320-767px
- Tablet: 768-1023px
- Desktop: 1024-1439px
- Wide: 1440px+

Core behavior:
- All 2-column sections collapse to single column below 1024px.
- Reading/order on mobile always prioritizes text before decorative visuals.
- Keep interactive targets at least 44x44px.
- Sticky nav remains compact; no more than one row on mobile.
- Avoid horizontal scroll at all breakpoints.

Container rules:
- Mobile horizontal padding: 16-20px
- Tablet: 24-32px
- Desktop: 40-64px

---

## Information Architecture

Single-page section order:
1. Hero
2. Expertise
3. Proof Block 1
4. Proof Block 2
5. Technical Philosophy
6. Contact

Navigation:
- Sticky top nav with section anchors
- Right side actions: GitHub, LinkedIn
- Active section indicator via subtle accent underline or dot

